contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|FBI}} '''[[FBI]]''' is the Federal Bureau of Investigation in the United States. '''FBI''' may also refer to: {{TOC right}} ==Film, television, and radio== * ''[[The FBI Story]]'', 1959 film about the Federal Bureau of Investigation * [[The F.B.I. (TV series)|''The F.B.I.'' (TV series)]], a 1965-1974 television series based in part on actual FBI cases * [[FBi Radio]], a community radio station based in Sydney, Australia * Fully booked interactive, a British children's TV show - a 2000 reformat of the series [[Fully Booked#FBi, 2000|''Fully Booked'']] ==Music== * FBI, an English soul band starring [[Rick Astley]] * [[F.B.I. (instrumental)|"F.B.I." (instrumental)]], a 1961 single by The Shadows * [[F.B.I. (album)|''F.B.I.'' (album)]], a song and album by The Dayton Family ==Organisations== * [[Full Blooded Italians]], a professional wrestling stable * [[Flying Buffalo]], a game publisher in Arizona * [[Federation of British Industries]], merged into Confederation of British Industry in 1965 ==Science== * [[FBI mnemonics]], for describing directions in magnetic fields * [[FBI transform]], for Fourier-Bros-Iaglonitzer transform, a concept in mathematics ==Books== *[[The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma]], short title "Fauna of British India". {{disambiguation}}
